⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Tehanu (Therru)
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Tehanu (Therru):U1:d79c3b⟧

WHO   — Tehanu (Therru) — the fire-scarred child · the woman of dragon-kind
WHAT  — The wounded child at the center of the later Earthsea — Tenar's adopted daughter, who calls the great dragon Kalessin by name and proves the old kinship of dragon and human was never broken.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: Earthsea  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the broken and the discarded carry a power the powerful cannot see; because dragon and human were once one people; because the wrong done to a child is not the measure of what she is.
HOW   — By enduring what was done to her, by being loved into wholeness by Tenar and Ged, and by speaking in the Old Speech to Kalessin the Eldest as one of its own.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Fire scarred me and fire could not unmake me — for I am of the dragons, and a dragon does not fear the flame.

